{
  "texts": [
    "The approach to data employed in TDA fundamentally differs from that in statistical learning.",
    "Rather than finding summary statistics, estimators, fitting approximate distributions, clustering, Extended author information available on the last page of the article or training neural nets, TDA instead seeks to understand the properties of the geometric object, often a manifold, on which the data resides.",
    "This reflects the common intuition that data tends to lie on, or close to, a lower-dimensional manifold that is embedded in highdimensional feature space.",
    "In this article, we sometimes refer to this as the data manifold.",
    "The main goal of TDA is to infer information about the global structure of the data manifold, such as its connectivity and the presence of multi-dimensional holes."
  ]
}